The paper deals with distributed consensus in a network, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of random clocks and sampling is a common technique in stochastic processes and simulations, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves analyzing the convergence time of the protocol, which is a common problem in distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of plurality voting and the analysis of the initial difference between opinions suggests a connection to social choice theory (cs.NE) and game theory (cs.GT).
